A bus with North Macedonian license plates crashed and erupted into flames around 2am local time as it was traveling on a freeway early on Tuesday, killing at least 45 people, interior ministry official Nikolai Nikolov told a local TV station. At least 45 people were killed after a bus caught fire and crashed, or crashed and then caught fire. At least 45 people were killed after a bus caught fire and crashed, or crashed and then caught fire. Some 12 children lost their lives in the accident, Bulgarian media reported. A handful of survivors, some of whom sustained severe burn injuries, were brought to a hospital in the Bulgarian capital of Sofia. The cause of the crash remains unknown. There were 52 people on the bus. According to Bulgarian media, all 50 passengers were Albanian nationals, while both drivers had North Macedonian passports. Think your friends would be interested? Share this story! 